{
  "10081000": {
    "Ah!<pc>Mr. Bocchan!  If you are Bocchan, he\ncame back a while ago but left\nimmediately. He said he was heading\n<br>\nout of the castle town, but he didn't\ngive a reason and seemed to be in a\nhurry.  I wonder what happened to him?": ""
  },
  "36592": {
    "Our leader, Siodore, has been thinking\ntirelessly about the means to protect\nhis people from Leidamates. A true\n<br>\nhero is a man like him.  Without you,\nthere would be no life.  Do not forget\nthis favor.": ""
  },
  "36593": {
    "Our leader, Master Thiodore, will\naccept us into Glen Castle without\ndistinction, as long as we are of the\n<br>\nsame race. Come, fugitives.  If you\nwish to see Master Thiodore, you must\nascend the stairs.": ""
  },
  "36594": {
    "Beyond you is the office of our\nleader, the great Master Thiodore.  If\nyou wish an audience, please enter.": ""
  },
  "36595": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>The people of the castle are tormented\nby insecurity.  It is not so much the\nleidermetes, but the hopelessness that\n<br>\nlies in the hearts and minds of the\npeople. If only the Boat Breaker\nhadn't stirred up such despair in the\n<br>\nhearts of the people.": ""
  },
  "36596": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Oh, my God. I'm so glad you came.\n I've been so busy with my burns that\nI've missed having someone to talk to.\n<br>\nMy dad seems to be busy, too. He's\nalways meeting with those wizards.  He\ndoesn't come to our room at all.": ""
  },
  "36597": {
    "It was about six months ago.  A man\nwas brought here once, using some\nunknown technique called Hajabneh.\n<br>\nWhen I asked him what his crime was,\nhe laughed and said he was just\ntalking to the leader. In the end, the\n<br>\nman was soon released from prison, but\nwhat he said to Master Siodore is\nstill a mystery.": ""
  },
  "36598": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_one><end_attr>What the hell! What's with Eldge? He\nbumps into people and doesn't even say\nsorry! He's always pissed me off but\n<br>\nlately he's really getting into his\nstride.": ""
  },
  "36599": {
    "This room? It's amazing, isn't it?  It\nused to be a weapons workshop. So they\nused a furnace this big to make\n<br>\nweapons.": ""
  },
  "36600": {
    "What do you want with this place?\n You'd better leave as soon as\npossible.": ""
  },
  "45065": {
    "The well is filled with water.": ""
  },
  "36601": {
    "As you know, there is a terrible\nshortage of water.  This single well\nsustains the lives of everyone who\n<br>\nlives in Glen Castle. My job is to\nmaintain this well.  Sometimes people\nhate me for it, but I'm proud to be a\n<br>\npart of it.": ""
  },
  "36602": {
    "I can't tell you how hard we worked to\nget those wizards to Glen Castle! At\nlast our efforts will bear fruit!  The\n<br>\ntime has come for man to defeat\nLeidameth!": ""
  },
  "36603": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv3><end_attr>Ha-ha-ha! That Eldge guy.  He's making\nme laugh when he says he's going to\ndestroy Leidametes! It seems he has\n<br>\nthe same big whack-job blood as his\ndead father!": ""
  },
  "36604": {
    "Are you referring to the location of\nEldge's room?  If so, it's the room\ndown the stairs, along the corridor to\n<br>\nthe left.": ""
  },
  "36605": {
    "Good grief.  Eldge must be in trouble\nif he's going to interfere in a grown-\nup's conversation. That greenhorn who\n<br>\nwent to see a tetralogist would have\nbeen turned away at the door.  It'll\nbe good medicine for him.": ""
  },
  "36606": {
    "I had heard that Bernhard, the\nshipwrecked wizard, was a renowned\nwizard who was summoned to the great\n<br>\nnation of Lendersia, Grand Zedorah.\nHowever, in the end, fame is no\nmeasure of a person's true ability, is\n<br>\nit?": ""
  },
  "36607": {
    "What on earth is Leidametes?  We don't\nreally know. To think that we would\nlightly try to destroy such an unknown\n<br>\nthing is a mere nonsense.": ""
  },
  "36608": {
    "Eldge's room is not this way.  It's\nthe other way around.  But what are we\ngoing to do with a guy like that?": ""
  },
  "36609": {
    "The people in the castle are tormented\nby anxiety.  Our job is to remove it.\nLet us prove that Leidermetes and\n<br>\ndoomsday prophecies are insignificant\nbefore the power of man.": ""
  },
  "36610": {
    "well<pc>I want to go back to the story with\nthe wizards.  I'd like to get back to\nthe wizards. If you have some business\n<br>\nto attend to, why don't you at least\ntalk to Eldge on the first floor of\nthe castle?": ""
  },
  "36611": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>Eldge traveled alone to perform the\nInheritance Ceremony?  Hmph! Leave\nsuch things to me.": ""
  },
  "37758": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv3><end_attr>Hmmm...that Eldge guy.  He's reckless\nto start talking about destroying\nLeidametes. He's headed northeast to\n<br>\nthe settlement of the Elves and the\nWeddies, but I wonder if that young\nchild will ever make it there.": ""
  },
  "36612": {
    "Eldge will be 10 years old this year.\n She should be able to see things\naround her by now. It's a problem,\n<br>\nisn't it?": ""
  },
  "36613": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>Eldge must be crazy to go outside Glen\nCastle all by himself! I know him!  He\ncan't even kill a slime!": ""
  },
  "36614": {
    "Nowadays, there is a terrible shortage\nof water everywhere in the world.  The\npeople of the glen owe their lives to\n<br>\nthe well in the castle.": ""
  },
  "36615": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>Seeing Lady Siodore's desperation, I\ncan't help but feel pain in my heart.\nHer only daughter, Claire, who was\n<br>\nseverely burned by the light of\nLeidametes, must be what is motivating\nher.": ""
  },
  "36616": {
    "You want water?  There is a room with\na well near Eldge's room.": ""
  },
  "36617": {
    "oh!<pc>I see.  I was worried about you when I\nheard you left the castle after Eldge.\nWhat? That the Elves and the Weddies\n<br>\nwere suffering from a water shortage?<pc>I'll be grateful for your report. I\nappreciate the report.  But I don't\nhave time to worry about other species\n<br>\nright now.": ""
  },
  "36618": {
    "<attr><feel_normal_one><end_attr>Oh, my! You're taking that water to\nthe elves' village? You're a real\nlooker.  If only we had a heart like\n<br>\nyours.<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "45066": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_one><end_attr>No, I won't say anything.": ""
  },
  "36619": {
    "<attr><feel_normal_one><end_attr>I see. You brought water to the elves'\nvillage? You are quite a sight to\nbehold.  If only we had a heart like\n<br>\nyours.<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "45067": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_one><end_attr>No, I won't say anything.": ""
  },
  "36620": {
    "Do not worry.  We must believe in\nThiodore. He will protect us with his\nlife, no matter what happens.": ""
  },
  "36621": {
    "You think this castle belongs to the\nOgre?  Well, you've met Gamilgo. The\nescapees in the castle don't know\n<br>\nanything about that.  They moved here\nafter we took Glen Castle. Do you\nblame us?  This castle is the only\n<br>\nthing that's kept these fugitives\nalive.": ""
  },
  "36622": {
    "<pc>Yes. Please pass.  Master Thiodore is\nin here.": ""
  },
  "36623": {
    "It seems that Eldge has gone out of\nthe castle with a very distressed look\non his face, but what is going on?": ""
  },
  "36624": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>It is all as you have heard.  We ruled\nthe castle under the command of Master\nSiodore and shime all the other races.\n<br>\nAnd we have accepted you escapees\nunder the pretense that this is the\ncastle of the humans.": ""
  },
  "36625": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv2><end_attr>You said you're going to start the\nwar?  Fine, I'll take it.  I'm still\nconfident with my sword. The world is\n<br>\ndoomed to be destroyed by Leidamates\nanyway.  I'm not afraid of what will\nhappen now!": ""
  },
  "36626": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>Ugh. It's so ugly.  We couldn't do\nanything!": ""
  },
  "36627": {
    "There used to be all kinds of races in\nGlen Castle.  But lately, I haven't\nseen any of them. They used to be my\n<br>\ndearest friends.  I've asked people\nwhy, but no one will tell me.": ""
  },
  "36628": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>What? You said my dad drove the other\ntribes out of Castle Glen?  That's\nterrible! Why would you tell such a\n<br>\nlie? Because Daddy is the kindest man\nin the world!  He's always helping me\nwhen I can't walk.": ""
  },
  "36629": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>The power of Leidermetes is much more\npowerful than we thought. It was just\nas the wicked Boat Master had said.\n<br>\n We had to cut off the source of the\nevil.": ""
  },
  "36630": {
    "Relax, relax, relax.  Even if\nLeidermetes falls, we'll be fine as\nlong as there's a wall of light. All\n<br>\nof you grown-ups are in such a hurry.\n It's so embarrassing.": ""
  },
  "36631": {
    "Water shortages and interspecies\nstrife were caused by the appearance\nof Leidametes in the world. Once\n<br>\nRaidametes is destroyed, there will be\nno need for humans to cling to Castle\nGlen.": ""
  },
  "36632": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv3><end_attr>Gahhhh! The war is about to start?\n That's great!  I'm not afraid of\nanything. What can a few ogres do?": ""
  },
  "36633": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv1><end_attr>If the Ogre wants to take Ikuya, I'll\ntake it.  A remnant of that size is\nnothing to be afraid of. Now, you,\n<br>\ntoo, can get out of here.  I'm not\nwrong.": ""
  },
  "36634": {
    "<attr><feel_angry_lv2><end_attr>What a surprise!  Gamilgo is going to\nstart Ikuya?<pc>Report. Thank you for your report.<br_break>": ""
  },
  "45068": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_one><end_attr>But I feel sorry for the escapees.\n They've been living here in Glen\nCastle without knowing what to expect.": ""
  },
  "36635": {
    "The art of the shipwreck. Nowadays, it\nis the only thing that can stand up to\nLeidermetes. We've been laughing at\n<br>\nBernhard for years, calling him a dog.\n It's a little too late for that now!": ""
  },
  "36636": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv2><end_attr>I heard the story!  I hear that Eldge\nhas headed for the Landon Mountains to\ndestroy Leidametes!<br_break>": ""
  },
  "45069": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv3><end_attr>Nun-nun. Now that the walls of light\nhave proved useless, the only hope for\nthe future is Eldge's shipwreck. But\n<br>\nhow can I entrust the future to Eldge\nafter calling my father a liar?": ""
  },
  "47808": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>We humans believed that we would be\nable to defeat Leidermetes, but was it\nhubris? But was it hubris?": ""
  },
  "36637": {
    "I'm surprised at Eldge at all.  It's\nas if he's a different person from\nwhen he ran out of here. I'm sure<pc>I guess the journey with the \"Mere Old\nMan\" changed Eldge.": ""
  },
  "36638": {
    "<pc>After Eldge left the castle, he came\nback to Glen Castle alone, looking\nexhausted and tired. I tried to call\n<br>\nout to him, but he ran to Master\nThiodore without a second thought.\nThinking back on it, I remember when\n<br>\nEldge was...<pc>You had just dropped off the \"Mere Old\nMan\" at Leidametes.": ""
  },
  "36639": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>You, a human, Eldge, and three\nsurgeons of other races.  Without any\nof them, this miracle could not have\n<br>\nhappened. How shallow we were to think\nwe could overcome the situation on our\nown. Now I can understand Mr.\n<br>\nBernhard's feelings for accepting the\nother races, even at odds with Master\nSiodore.": ""
  },
  "36640": {
    "He bowed deeply to Master Thiodore\n The sight of Eldge<pc>I wish I could have shown it to you. I\nwould have had to believe in you with\nall my heart.  No. Friendship is a\n<br>\ngood thing, isn't it?": ""
  },
  "36641": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv2><end_attr>I wonder what my hometown looks like\nnow.  I'm happy to be able to go home,\nbut I'm also afraid to see my hometown\n<br>\nin ruins. But I'm happy that I have\nlife.  I have to do my best to live\nfor those who have passed away.": ""
  },
  "36642": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>I am sure Mr. Bernhard was very happy.\nHe had such a wonderful son.": ""
  },
  "36643": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>Seeing you and Eldge, my father\nrealized how important it is to work\ntogether and changed his mind. I have\n<br>\nto do my best to get better.  It's\ngoing to be hard from now on.  I want\nto be able to help you.": ""
  },
  "36644": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv1><end_attr>We wanted to make ourselves look\nstrong by laughing at Bernhard.  It's\na boondoggle, isn't it?": ""
  },
  "36645": {
    "<attr><feel_sad_lv3><end_attr>Wait a minute!  You're pulling me out\nof Castle Glen? You're not just gonna\nleave me here like this, are you?\n<br>\n Hey! Let me out!": ""
  },
  "36646": {
    "I bumped into Eldge earlier.  Then he\napologized even though it was my\nfault. That's weird. She never\n<br>\napologized herself.": ""
  },
  "36647": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv3><end_attr>Ha-ha-ha. As for us who came all the\nway to Glen Castle, we ended up with a\nrather pathetic result, didn't we?<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "45070": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>But just to see your courageous faces\nwas worth the effort of coming to this\ncountry.": ""
  },
  "36648": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Finally, the day has come when I can\nreturn this weapons workshop to its\nrightful owners.  I'm sure that\n<br>\nmagnificent furnace is pleased.": ""
  },
  "36649": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv3><end_attr>Well! I must get ready to leave this\ncastle.<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "45071": {
    "<attr><feel_think_lv3><end_attr>However, I feel like I'm forgetting\nsomething important. Huh.": ""
  },
  "36650": {
    "When I see those who have stayed at\nCastle Glen return to their hometowns,\nI, too, will leave for some faraway\n<br>\nplace. From now on, it will be young\npeople like you who will lead the\npeople of the world.<pc>You were heroes.  You have been true\nheroes.  I thank you from the bottom\nof my heart.": ""
  },
  "36651": {
    "We have an important task ahead of us,\nto send the people of Glen back to\ntheir homelands.  This is our chance\n<br>\nto redeem ourselves.": ""
  },
  "36652": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv3><end_attr><pc>I will never forget you in my life. I\nwill never forget you in my life.\n Thanks to you, I met Himea and\n<br>\nGarmie. You guys taught me so many\nthings.  True strength, the will to do\nthings.  And the meaning of true\n<br>\npride. Himea and Garmie still come to\nvisit me from time to time. Through\nthem, I'm getting to know more and\n<br>\nmore people from other races. That's\nwhy we'll be okay now.  We won't\nfalter here. I promise you. I will\n<br>\nsurely deliver the art of the Unbroken\nBoat to your time.  So you must\npromise me too. Even if we live in\n<br>\ndifferent eras, you and I will always\nbe friends!": ""
  },
  "36653": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv2><end_attr>Mr. Bernhard said.  He said that\nBocchan will eventually acquire the\npower to surpass even himself. I am\n<br>\nsure that Mr. Bernhard is rejoicing\nover Bocchan's success in heaven.": ""
  },
  "36654": {
    "A picture of a man on a wrecked boat\nis pasted on the wall.": ""
  },
  "36655": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr><pc>I'm glad you're here!  Welcome aboard.\nWell, with that face, you've finally\nmade it! Hey.<pc>Oh, my God!  I'm sure that the art of\nthe shipwreck will serve you well.<bw_break>": ""
  },
  "45072": {
    "<attr><feel_happy_lv1><end_attr>No, I don't want to. I'm not going to\ndo it after all.  I won't ask about\nthe future.  I'm just trying to\n<br>\nfulfill my promise to you. Life here\nis still tough.  But we've started\nhelping each other out, and that seems\n<br>\nto be helping us get through it.\nThanks to Himea, Garmie, and you, who\nare still popping up here and there.\n<br>\n With this, I'm sure the future will\nbe<pc>So promise me. So you have to promise\nme too.  Even if we live in different\ntimes, you and I will always be\n<br>\nfriends!": ""
  }
}